<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span>g the Mandet, as they Knew it was to receive, and not to <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[ho]</span>wever I got 23 Skins Credits from them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>s soon as they were placed, I treated them with a Bottle of Shrub, of which they thought a great Deal, and then begun to make a Speech to them on the Useal Topics, thanking them that behaved well to my people last year, and telling them, that while they Continued to behave so, that I should take Care, they should never want where with to Cover themselves from the inclemency of the weather, and bring up their Children<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey were very proude of this Compliment being paid them in presence of the Other Indians<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>fter that, I begun to Animadvert with the Others, On their inconsistency and false promises that Some of them had made me before, and that it was perhaps with a View to deceive me again, that they wanted me to leave people there, that after they got wherewith to Enable them to pass the Winter, they would forget that they were beholding to my Goods, Iron Works, and Ammunition for their Hunt, and Only think of takeing their Skins to Osnaburgh or Else where, without pay above the half of their Credits, or Considering in the least, the Quantity of Liquor, Tobacco, Ammunition, Knives, flints &amp;c, bestowed on them <span class="AddHand-editors">[in]</span> the course of the fall, Witer, &amp; Spring, while the English</p>

